WEBVTT

00:04.666 --> 00:05.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.766 --> 00:07.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.766 --> 00:10.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
a White House shakeup
at the highest level.

00:10.600 --> 00:15.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump picks Secretary
of Homeland Security John Kelly
as his new chief of staff,

00:16.733 --> 00:17.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
replacing Reince Priebus.

00:17.866 --> 00:18.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Then:

00:18.866 --> 00:20.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

00:20.900 --> 00:22.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: This is, you know,
clearly a disappointing moment.

00:22.933 --> 00:25.000 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A
dramatic defeat.

00:25.000 --> 00:29.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The U.S. Senate fails
to pass health care
reform in an overnight
vote, dealing a painful

00:31.366 --> 00:34.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
blow to the president
and the Republican Party.

00:34.333 --> 00:36.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And it's Friday.

00:36.500 --> 00:39.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Mark Shields and David
Brooks weigh in on all
these developments,
capping yet another

00:39.833 --> 00:43.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
tumultuous week for the
Trump administration.

00:43.033 --> 00:48.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then: Detroit's violent past
put to paint - - how the
deadly 1967 riots inspire a new

00:50.933 --> 00:53.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
generation of artists
in the Motor City.

00:53.400 --> 00:55.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRINA CHATMAN, Curator,
Charles H. Wright Museum
of African-American
History: You see

00:55.366 --> 00:59.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the emotions of the
artists, describing history
from their perspective.

00:59.366 --> 01:00.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I see the politics.

01:00.900 --> 01:05.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I see the social concerns
that people had in it.

01:05.333 --> 01:06.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I see their pain.

01:06.800 --> 01:11.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:12.766 --> 01:14.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:14.966 --> 01:19.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Reince Priebus
is out as White House chief of
staff tonight, after just six

01:27.066 --> 01:29.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
months on the job.

01:29.066 --> 01:33.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump announced in
a tweet late today that John
Kelly, the secretary of homeland

01:33.800 --> 01:35.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
security, will take his place.

01:35.966 --> 01:40.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president had more to say
after returning from a day trip
to New York, a trip that Priebus

01:41.466 --> 01:43.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
was on.

01:43.166 --> 01:46.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP, President
of the United States:
Reince is a good man.

01:46.100 --> 01:49.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
John Kelly will do
a fantastic job.

01:49.266 --> 01:54.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
General Kelly has been a star,
done an incredible job thus far,
respected by everybody, a great,

01:56.633 --> 01:57.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
great American.

01:57.633 --> 01:58.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Reince Priebus, a good man.

01:58.633 --> 02:00.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

02:00.833 --> 02:05.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And to help
unpack what led to this change
at the top, I'm joined now

02:05.066 --> 02:10.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by Robert Costa, reporter
for The Washington
Post and moderator of
"Washington Week" here

02:10.533 --> 02:11.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on PBS.

02:11.300 --> 02:13.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Welcome, Robert.

02:13.366 --> 02:15.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And as I go to you, I'm going
to share with everybody just
briefly what the president's

02:15.733 --> 02:17.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tweets were.

02:17.833 --> 02:20.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He tweeted -- this was late
this afternoon - - he said: "I
am pleased to inform you that

02:20.100 --> 02:24.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I just named General
Secretary John F. Kelly as
White House chief of staff.

02:24.666 --> 02:27.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He's a great American
and great leader.

02:27.100 --> 02:31.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He said: "John has also
done a spectacular job
at Homeland Security.

02:31.533 --> 02:34.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He's been a true star
of my administration."

02:34.000 --> 02:37.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And finally, he said: "I would
like to thank Reince Priebus
for his service and dedication

02:37.500 --> 02:38.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to this country.

02:38.900 --> 02:42.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We accomplished a lot together
and I'm proud of him!"

02:42.466 --> 02:44.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But I guess it didn't work out.

02:44.600 --> 02:47.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: It was a sudden
change, Judy, but it was also
a change that was in the works

02:47.666 --> 02:49.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for months.

02:49.766 --> 02:53.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president brought on Reince
Priebus because he saw him as
a whisperer to House speaker,

02:53.466 --> 02:57.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Paul Ryan, a close friend of
Priebus from Wisconsin and
he thought Priebus could help

02:57.266 --> 02:59.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
get his legislative
agenda through.

02:59.566 --> 03:03.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But as that agenda stalled on
health care and other fronts,
he began to muse in recent

03:03.600 --> 03:07.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
months with friends about
perhaps making a change at
the top of the White House.

03:07.666 --> 03:11.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kelly has been at the forefront
of his mind because he's
not a dramatic future and he

03:11.766 --> 03:14.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has executed for the president
on immigration policy.

03:14.033 --> 03:17.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There have
been so many ups and downs,
as you know very well, because

03:17.666 --> 03:20.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you have been covering it every
day, for this White House.

03:20.600 --> 03:25.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How did the president
see Reince Priebus as
connected to that or not?

03:25.033 --> 03:27.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Did he blame him for
what's been going on?

03:27.000 --> 03:30.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: He thought
Priebus, because he had run the
Republican National Committee,

03:30.700 --> 03:32.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
could be a stabilizing force.

03:32.700 --> 03:36.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But Priebus as RNC chairman
was always a low-key presence.

03:36.366 --> 03:41.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He wasn't who was known for
managing a large organization
in a military-style fashion.

03:42.833 --> 03:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president wanted that
kind of person to come in.

03:44.733 --> 03:47.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's important to note
that Kelly has a strong
relationship with Jared Kushner,

03:47.933 --> 03:51.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the senior adviser, and
actually Steve Bannon,
the chief strategist.

03:51.533 --> 03:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they represent the two poles
in this warring White House.

03:54.700 --> 03:59.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So there is an expectation now
from my sources that Kelly can
come in and try to be a calming

04:00.233 --> 04:02.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
force.

04:02.266 --> 04:04.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You mentioned
the two poles, but we also
had the announcement the other

04:04.300 --> 04:08.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
day from the president he is
bringing in a new communications
director, Anthony Scaramucci,

04:09.733 --> 04:12.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
who has been in a
very visible war.

04:12.333 --> 04:17.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the language that he used
in that conversation with a "New
Yorker" magazine reporter was

04:20.300 --> 04:23.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
making all kind of news
headlines yesterday.

04:23.033 --> 04:25.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How does that fit into all this?

04:25.133 --> 04:28.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: No, it's a smart
observation, because it does
seem incongruent to have this

04:28.566 --> 04:33.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
swashbuckling New Yorker in
Anthony Scaramucci now working
alongside General Kelly, who is

04:34.766 --> 04:36.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
known for being a
very precise man.

04:36.866 --> 04:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it really reflects how the
president is trying to turn to
his loyalists from New York,

04:40.600 --> 04:44.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as well as to military figures
as he tries to right the ship.

04:44.866 --> 04:49.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He knows his health care
legislation is going nowhere
right now on Capitol Hill.

04:49.400 --> 04:54.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He's trying to recover
his presidency, turning
to two different types,
the New Yorkers and

04:55.100 --> 04:57.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the military.

04:57.200 --> 05:00.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, does this
look to you, Robert, like
this is a team that can work

05:00.000 --> 05:05.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
smoothly together, that can get
this White House back on some
semblance of a normal track?

05:06.966 --> 05:09.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: Well, General
Kelly has said publicly in
the past that he would like to

05:09.366 --> 05:14.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
maybe try to monitor the
president's calls, that
he thinks there could
be more organization

05:14.233 --> 05:16.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
inside of the West Wing.

05:16.366 --> 05:19.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's going to be interesting
to see if he can really try
to contain the Oval Office.

05:19.133 --> 05:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is an Oval Office
that's known for having
a lot of entryway, people
coming in and offering

05:23.433 --> 05:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their advice, often
unsolicited, to the president.

05:26.233 --> 05:30.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If Kelly can get ahold of that
in a way Priebus never did,
maybe he can turn it around.

05:30.366 --> 05:34.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But he also has to navigate
all the different circles
around President Trump.

05:34.133 --> 05:37.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is someone who is known
not just for having a
straight chain of command.

05:37.200 --> 05:39.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He talks to a lot of
people all the time.

05:39.266 --> 05:42.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, speaking
of which, what one hears is
that this is a president who

05:42.466 --> 05:44.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
really likes to be his
own chief of staff.

05:44.000 --> 05:45.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT COSTA: Indeed.

05:45.266 --> 05:46.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: He likes
-- he's a detail person.

05:46.800 --> 05:50.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He wants to know what everybody
is doing, how they're doing it.

05:50.100 --> 05:52.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How is likely to fit with
somebody like General Kelly?

05:52.433 --> 05:56.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: General Kelly
doesn't have a deep personal
relationship with President

05:56.333 --> 05:57.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Trump.

05:57.466 --> 05:59.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Will he stop the
president from tweeting?

05:59.300 --> 06:01.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's what all my
sources want to know.

06:01.533 --> 06:05.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Can he actually stop
the president from, as
you say, being his own
chief of staff, being

06:05.166 --> 06:07.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
his own spokesman?

06:07.633 --> 06:10.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For now, it seems like
Scaramucci and others
are channeling the
president in their public

06:10.266 --> 06:12.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
presentation, not
trying to hold him back.

06:12.233 --> 06:15.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The other thing,
Robert, I have to raise are
the so-called -- what the

06:15.566 --> 06:19.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
White House and the president
like to call the leaks which
they say are coming from a

06:19.933 --> 06:24.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lot of people in the White
House and the administration
that shouldn't be, but
then the stories one

06:26.866 --> 06:29.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also hears that not only is
the president talking to the
press, but people at the highest

06:29.633 --> 06:31.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
levels in the White House.

06:31.566 --> 06:34.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How is all that likely to change
or not as a result of this?

06:34.700 --> 06:38.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: It's a very
messy situation, because the
president is furious behind the

06:38.400 --> 06:40.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
scenes.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's telling his aides that
they need to stop the leaks,
but often these leaks are coming

06:42.600 --> 06:45.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
from some of his own
White House officials.

06:45.200 --> 06:50.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there's a big difference
between intelligence
community leaks and leaks
about palace intrigue

06:50.933 --> 06:52.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
inside of the West Wing.

06:52.900 --> 06:55.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But a lot of the president's
aides are just trying to reflect
his own unhappiness about

06:55.800 --> 06:58.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a White House he thinks
that is talking too much.

06:58.033 --> 07:01.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, it is --
as you and I were just saying,
it's one more tumultuous

07:01.566 --> 07:03.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
day in what's been
nonstop tumult.

07:03.600 --> 07:06.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT COSTA: And everyone was
thinking maybe Attorney General
Sessions would be the person

07:06.866 --> 07:10.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to go at the end of this week,
after all of his struggles
with President Trump, but it

07:10.400 --> 07:12.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was Priebus.

07:12.400 --> 07:15.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we don't
know what is going to happen
to the attorney general at this

07:15.166 --> 07:16.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
point.

07:16.166 --> 07:17.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT COSTA: We do not.

07:17.166 --> 07:19.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Robert Costa, thanks.

07:19.166 --> 07:20.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you're going to have much
more on "Washington Week"
on all these PBS stations.

07:20.200 --> 07:21.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

07:21.200 --> 07:23.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT COSTA: Thank you.

07:23.266 --> 07:26.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And now to the
day's other big story, and
that is the collapse of Senate

07:26.933 --> 07:29.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Republican efforts to
pass a health care bill.

07:29.866 --> 07:34.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
A last-ditch effort
for a partial repeal of
Obamacare failed by a
single vote early today,

07:36.433 --> 07:38.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
frustrating Republican
leaders and the president.

07:38.900 --> 07:41.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Lisa Desjardins
begins our coverage.

07:41.500 --> 07:46.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: President Trump
today showed no sign of backing
down, despite the stunning

07:47.666 --> 07:49.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Senate defeat.

07:49.733 --> 07:51.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of
the United States: They should
have approved health care last

07:51.500 --> 07:53.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
night, but you can't
have everything.

07:53.900 --> 07:55.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Boy, oh, boy.

07:55.433 --> 07:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have been working on
that one for seven years.

07:57.600 --> 07:58.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Can you believe that?

07:58.600 --> 07:59.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
The swamp.

07:59.600 --> 08:02.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But we will get it done.

08:02.500 --> 08:04.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're going get it done.

08:04.466 --> 08:07.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: At an event for
police officers in Ronkonkoma,
New York, he was blunt.

08:07.333 --> 08:12.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP: You
know, I said from the
beginning, let Obamacare
implode, and then do it.

08:13.666 --> 08:16.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I turned out to be right.

08:16.466 --> 08:17.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let Obamacare implode.

08:17.766 --> 08:19.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

08:19.266 --> 08:23.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: All this after
the Senate's overnight drama.

08:25.266 --> 08:26.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Outside the Capitol stood
a crowd of protesters.

08:26.600 --> 08:28.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Inside, around 10:00 p.m.

08:28.666 --> 08:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last night, Republicans had
