of African-American History.

42:53.500 --> 42:57.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Striking images of
confrontation, and consequences,
in works by national
and local artists from

42:59.533 --> 43:00.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the 1960s on.

43:00.966 --> 43:03.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Curator Patrina Chatman:

43:03.400 --> 43:05.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRINA CHATMAN, Curator,
Charles H. Wright Museum
of African-American
History: You see

43:05.333 --> 43:07.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the emotions of the
artists, describing history
from their perspective.

43:07.966 --> 43:09.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I see the politics.

43:09.433 --> 43:13.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I see the social concerns
that people had in it.

43:13.800 --> 43:15.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I see their pain.

43:15.766 --> 43:20.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I see and I feel their
pain, and I think other
people will feel it as well.

43:22.566 --> 43:26.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: July, 1967,
